programmes.show_description: This Is CBeebies. Programmes start at 6.00am.
Comic Cut. Tish is saddened to find out her favourite comic is no longer being published.
Hippity Hoppity, Voosh. Children's animation. Bing and Sula are playing a vooshing game with their favourite toys. They throw them into the air to see how high they can fly.
Honk Honk. Preschool series. The Teletubbies hear a 'honk honk' and the Tubby Car approaches. The Tubby Car drives them across Teletubbyland as they sing the Tubby Car song.
Hero Time. When Tee doesn't want to help tidy the house, Mo becomes the superhero 'Monkey Mum' to make the jobs fun.
Turnip of Terror. Supertato and the Veggies are shocked when they meet a turnip in the deli counter.
Helping Hoppity. Bing, Sula and Pando are playing superheroes in the park.
X Marks the Swop. The treasure of the Knights of Swoppiton awaits! If only Mojo and Bo could find it.
Campfire Choir. Today at Squirrel Club, there are all sorts of comparisons to learn - from small to smallest, hungry to hungriest, and Duggee to Duggiest!
The Big Day Out Badge. Duggee takes the Squirrels and their parents on an exciting mystery trip.
Housework. Mum and Dad vow to only finish their boring housework when the kids stop acting silly!
Queens. During a game of queens, Bluey and Bingo find that playing the butler is much more fun. But someone must play the queen, even if it means not being afraid of a bit of hard work.
The Continent of Africa. Glitch and Tala get lost in Africa. Can the Go Jetters find them in this huge continent?
The Tale of the Brewing Storm. Animated series. Peter, Lily and Benjamin race to rescue Cotton-tail's beloved blanket, escape Mr Tod and get back home before a brewing storm breaks.
Kauri Forest. The Octonauts must track down some Australian possums and help them to return home.
You're Five Ones and I'm Five Tens. Superstar Fifty sings a song that shows Five the patterns that make them similar in so many ways - if you can count to five, you can count to fifty!
Top. When T gets stuck on top of a mountain, A, E, I, O and U come to the rescue.   Followed by Tiny Wonders.
Superhero. Test your superpowers with my awesome Superhero Challenge. We've assembled climbers, squats and runners. The supervillain is the Activate!
Peas. Bella and Lift visit the Fortress of Fun, where Kingsley and Queenie have fun looking for peas with the Playtimers in their Pea Party game.
Fig. Live from the Roots and Fruits theatre, it's the nicest, kindest Fig, performing his song Just Can't Help Being Sweet!
Voosh! Children's animation. Bing is vooshing with Hoppity around the garden, making him fly higher and higher. With one particularly enthusiastic throw, Hoppity disappears.
Kite. Dee encourages a friend to say 'kite', and we go on a whirlwind word adventure. We see a flying kite, a roaring kite, a dragon kite and even a snoring kite!
Gotcha! Declan upsets Lu and Barnaby when he doesn't play by the rules.
Cesar's Big Idea. Cesar has a great idea, but maybe he is aiming too high.
More About In and Out. Stop-motion preschool programme. A man is looking at his phone. He puts it in his briefcase. The Twirlywoos pass the phone to the man every time it rings.
Superheroes. Educational series using Makaton sign language. Justin and his friend pretend to be superheroes. Super Tumble rescues Shopkeeper Tumble, Baker Tumble and Aunt Polly.
Snowball. Preschool series. It is snowing in Teletubbyland! The Teletubbies find big snowballs, dance with a snowman and watch children make a caterpillar out of snow.
Superheroes. Gemma, Benjee Bear and Bailee Bear invite little ones and their grown-ups to explore superheroes through play, song and story. Toddlers and grown-ups at home can join in too!
Urban Park. Elsee meets her new friend Jacob in the city and plays a game of I-spy.
Raindrops. When rain threatens to spoil a family camping trip, Maddie and Triggs receive a visit from a happy little raindrop, who soon has the whole gang dancing around the tent.
Cookie Baker. Dylan the cookie baker wants to make enough cookies for all his customers. But when the line gets super long, he needs to find a way to speed things up!
Uncle Lou. Lou babysits some squawking little birds who drive him crazy.
Hibernation. Ginger and the Pea-Rexes accidentally wake up a Kiwimammuthus during a snowball fight.
The Dump. On a trip to the dump, Dad claims he's the best at everything.
The Cheese Badge. Duggee and the Squirrels go on a mission to contain an outbreak.
Dress Up Day. Love Monster and Tiniest Fluffiest Bunny create their own superhero and supervillain characters for Dress Up Day, but their fun threatens to ruin the day for everyone else.
Timmy the Hero. Timmy's imagination is sparked when he reads a superhero comic.
Eden and Ava Are Superheroes! Eden and Ava pretend to be superheroes! They go on a mission to rescue a toy that's become lost in the woods. But will the heroes find the toy and save the day?
Jake's Australian Meat Pie. Jake is making traditional Australian meat pies filled with lamb mince.

programmes.show_name: Ferne and Rory's Teeny Tiny Creatures
programmes.show_description: Bumblebees. Ferne learns how bumblebees help grow food. Rory and Sandy build a bumblebee home.
Mission: Transport Museum. Kika needs her supersight on a family day out at the Woofton Transport Museum.
Tamarin and Crowned Pigeon. Aneeshwar and Lizzie meet cotton-top tamarins and the Victoria crowned pigeon.
Superheroes. Biff and Anneena are playing superheroes, but Kipper can't find his special superpower.
Puffin Practice. Oona tries to teach Baba how to be a grown-up puffin.
Imagination (Give It a Try). Animated series about a group of singing potatoes. The potatoes discover the amazing things you can do when you give imagination a try.
Two Frogs and the Toad. When Yukee's Garden plays host to Ray and Easy, the Jazz Frogs, Toad discovers he has had an unlikely influence over their visitors.
The Making Friends Badge. Animated preschool series. The Squirrels go to a jamboree where they meet another group of young animals with their very own version of Duggee.
z. Dee encourages a friend to say 'z', and we go on an adventure around the sound. We see some zips, do some zooming and see some zebras crossing a road!
Heroes with Zeroes. When there's trouble in space, Ten and the Ten Times Table rocket to the rescue.
Plusman. Educational fun. Plusman to the rescue! A new superhero arrives in Alphaland to save the day by joining words together.
Star Chart. Justin meets two Irish dancing stars, while Mr Tumble earns stars for his star chart.
Custard Chaos. Preschool series. The Tubby Custard Machine careers crazily out of Home Dome and goes on a messy ride around Teletubbyland.
Patchwork Hummingbird. Patchwork Hummingbird has a problem: he wants to drink sweet nectar but the flowers are closed! Will the Patchwork Pals find a way to help him?
Raa Raa and the Jingly Jangly Jungle Band. Animation set in the Jingly Jangly Jungle. Raa Raa becomes the singer in Crocky's Jingly Jangly Jungle Band.
My Hero. When Brewster's hero can't make it for Hero Day, he and Zephie set off on their own hero duty and learn what makes a real hero along the way. .
Episode 17. Comedy sketch show for younger viewers. Captain Adorable is on hand with another top tip for his new trainee Awesome Girl - this time he shows her some very silly ways to hide.
Building Machines. Grace shows off three amazing machines that all help build things.
The Upside-Down Map. The Game Catchers land on the Perfume Planet and learn to play the train race.
Lionfish. Animated deep sea adventures with Captain Barnacles and his explorers. The Octonauts get more than they bargained for with a pair of invasive lionfish.
The Tale of the Hero Rabbit. Animated series. Benjamin gets more than he bargained for when a band of desperate mice mistake him for a hero.
The Super Squirrel Badge. Animated preschool series. The Squirrels decide they want to be superheroes. Is there anyone that needs their help?
Juno's No Nap Day. Juno decides to give up napping but soon has a cranky meltdown, as she is so tired.
The Dough Blob. Evil Pea makes a giant dough blob so that she can take over the supermarket. The Tato Team must use some baking know-how to save the day.
Mission Bat. The Ducklings try to get rid of a bat that has interrupted their game. But Weasy thinks it's supercool and ditches the Ducklings to become a comic book hero with a bat sidekick.
Mojo Drop the Ball. Mojo and Bo's wrecking ball might destroy a lot more than it's supposed to!
Housework. Mum and Dad vow to only finish their boring housework when the kids stop acting silly!
Sleepytime. Bingo and Floppy have an intergalactic adventure in Bingo's dream, while the rest of her sleep-deprived family try to navigate Bingo's nonstop night-time bed-hopping.
Super Nugget. Nugget reinvents herself as a comic book hero called Super Nugget, but Pancake is dismissive of her new hobby as defender of the berg. The others persuade him to think again.
Andy and the Elephant Shrew. Preschool wildlife series. Mr Hammond has asked Andy to give a talk about elephant shrews. Andy heads to the African savannah to find the tiny creature.
Waffle and George. Preschool comedy drama series. Mrs Hobbs's cat George gets locked inside her house, giving Waffle a chance to prove himself to Mrs Hobbs. Can he rescue George?
The Mermaid Wish. Rafi's mermaid wish helps Jake find his courage, and they have a fun underwater tea party.
It's Time to Be a Superhero. JoJo and Gran Gran are at the library for the Super Saleem book launch, while JoJo wonders what makes a superhero and what her superpower may be.
Pond Prose. Animation. Sarah is inspired by listening to a poetry record and decides to make up some poetry of her own.
Small to the Rescue. Small comes to the rescue when Granny, Major, Mother and the Soup Dragon get into trouble.
Hiccup. BaBa has the hiccups. MeMo helps to make them disappear before BeddyByes time.
Sneezing. In a magical forest, colourful characters have adventures. Igglepiggle lets out a very big sneeze and soon Upsy Daisy and the Tombliboos are sneezing too.
Luke Evans - Even Superheroes Make Mistakes. Luke Evans tells a powerful Bedtime Story about how even the most super of superheroes can make mistakes, just like the rest of us!
This Is CBeebies. Programmes start at 6.00am.
Play with Us. Tish says she will be Dad for the day while Tash is Tish and Bobby is... Bobby.
Talkie Taxi. Children's animation. Bing and Sula discover a new toy at Amma's creche - a talking ride-on car. It seems like fun until talkie taxi keeps saying the same thing.
Not Enough Room. Preschool series. The Teletubbies are about to go on the Tubby Custard Ride with the hat, bag, ball and scooter when they realise there is not enough room.
Dance. Preschool animation. Tee and Mo are enjoying a dancing day - until Tee notices someone laughing at them. Can Mo get Tee to dance like no-one's watching again?
Veggies Gotta Dance. Supertato and Evil Pea face each other in a dance-off so Supertato can rescue his friends.
Skipping. Coco is teaching Bing and Sula how to skip. Sula starts to get quite good at it, but Bing finds it difficult and gets frustrated. Can Coco and Sula help Bing learn to skip?
Cliffhanger. Felix the pig is stuck on a cliff ledge where not even Mojo's tops can reach him. They will need to be creative to get Bo up there and save that poor pig!
Stick Time. How many siblings does Norrie have? What's Duggee's favourite badge? What does everyone do on Fridays? Squirrel Club has the answers!
The Tree Badge. Duggee helps the Squirrels learn about all the amazing things trees do for the creatures who live among them, and earn their tree badges in the process!
Pass the Parcel. Lucky's dad changes the rules of pass the parcel back to having one prize in the middle.
Flat-Pack. While Mum and Dad struggle to build new flat-pack furniture, Bluey and Bingo transform the empty boxes into their own new world.
The Continent of Europe. The Go Jetters help Grandmaster Glitch take his own souvenir selfies across Europe.
The Tale of the Flying Rabbits. Animated series. When Peter learns that his father once crash-landed a flying machine into Mr McGregor's garden, he vows to find it and pilot it home!
Sea Turtle's Shell. When a sea turtle loses a chunk of its shell, Tweak and Bud must engineer a solution.
The Forest of Tens. Thirty-Six and Forty-Five are exploring the Forest of Tens on a special quest. But what is the special something they need to find and bring to Ten?
Why. Young Y wants to know why he can't sing with the vowels.   Followed by Tiny Wonders.
Mountain. Reach new heights in my soaring Mountain Challenge! Climb your way through lunges, climbers and knee smashers, followed by the Activate.
Towel. Bella plays funny games with Lift using her colourful towel. Together, they visit Hettie in the Ice Disco, who uses a big towel to make up a new dance - the Butterfly Boogie!
Mango. Live from the Roots and Fruits theatre, it's the magical wish granter Mango, ready to make all the cast wishes come true!
Nature Explorer. Children's animation. Bing and his friends play nature explorers in Amma's garden by spinning a giant colour wheel and then finding something of that colour.
Octopus. Dee encourages a friend to say 'octopus', and we go on a whirlwind word adventure. We see lots of different octopuses - an orange octopus, a giant octopus and even a clever octopus!
Sing Along. Lu upsets Barnaby when she co-opts his favourite song.
The Squawk Squawk. The Piggies build a nest for a giant bird that doesn't actually exist.
More About Stretching. Stop-motion preschool programme. A man is packing his suitcase ready for a holiday and stretches his swimming goggles and trunks before packing them.
Getting Sporty. Educational series using Makaton sign language. Today, Justin and his friends learn how to boogie board while Mr Tumble plays a game of tennis with Lord Tumble.
Packing. Preschool series. Tinky Winky puts Dipsy's hat in the bag - and Noo-noo hoovers them both up! The children in Tummy Tales pack a bag for an overnight stay with a relative.
Yellow. Giovanna and Baby Bear invite babies and their grown-ups to explore objects that are yellow through discovery, play, song and story. Babies and grown-ups at home can join in too!
Dentist. Elsee visits a dentist and plays I-spy with her new friend Shanaya.
Bicycle Bell. A bicycle ride with Dad soon turns into an intergalactic space adventure. Maddie and Triggs imagine themselves as brave explorers, shooting like rockets into the unknown.
House Mover. Dylan the house mover wants to help a customer move into their new home. But when something goes missing, he really needs to get moving!
Especially Special Day. Kiri has to overcome her jealousy when everyone gives Lou presents.
Just Dig It. A Mandarinteryx has moved into home base and is causing a big mess.
Zoo. Bluey's backyard zoo is home to wonderful animals, especially the big blue daddy gorilla. But when he grabs visitor Bingo and escapes, zookeeper Bluey must recapture the wild beast.
The Radio Badge. The Squirrels find some of Duggee's radio equipment and decide to start their own show.
On the Hunt for Boonloons. The best game to play on a planet with crocodile aliens is crush the balloon!
Timmy Goes Camping. Animated adventures of a lamb at nursery school. Harriet and Osbourne take the class to a field where they have put up a tent, but Timmy will not join in.
Kyra and Khloe: Princesses and Crocodiles. Kyra and Khloe enjoy some pretend play with crocodiles, leaf monsters, and an evil queen!
Choekyi's Tibetan Spinach Momos. Choekyi's momos are a type of dumpling filled with spinach, cheese and mushrooms.

programmes.show_name: Ferne and Rory's Teeny Tiny Creatures
programmes.show_description: Spiders. Ferne meets a tarantula. Rory and Sandy look for superhero spiders in the garden.
Mission: Talent Show. Therapy dog Toffee and his owner Helen help Betty and Pop-Pop feel brave enough to perform at their talent show at the Woofton Care Home.
Dhole and Dwarf Mongoose. Aneeshwar and Lizzie meet two amazing animals and reveal a surprising connection between them. This time, it's the dhole and the dwarf mongoose.
Waffle Needs Quiet Time. Waffle learns that reading can be just as much fun as noisy maze games.
The Mystery Egg. Oona, Baba and Mossy babysit a little egg and help find its mama and papa.
Chip's Theme. Animated series about a group of singing potatoes. Chip sings a heartfelt song about being a potato. Though he can't do many physical things, he is proud of who he is.
The Sunflower and the Bee. When a bee interrupts the gang's sunflower-growing contest, the results are unexpectedly musical!
The River Badge. Animated preschool series. Duggee has a package that needs delivering right to the other end of the river, a long way from the clubhouse.
Banana. Preschool series about words. Dee encourages a friend to say 'banana', and we go on a whirlwind word adventure exploring what bananas look and taste like.
Five's Handy Shop. Five opens a handy new shop and helps her friends learn the value of money and how to combine lots of pennies into bigger ones.
Odd. Educational fun. O goes through the magnifying glass to where the grass is blue, the trees are square and nonsense words make friendly monsters!
Hairdressers. Educational series using Makaton sign language. Justin and his friends go for a haircut today, while Mr Tumble has lots of messy fun pretending to be a hairdresser.
Tallest Shortest. Preschool series. The Teletubbies see who is the tallest and who is the shortest, and the children in Tummy Tales put themselves in height order.
Patchwork Squirrel. The Patchwork Pals have a problem. Squirrel is collecting all the nuts but only for himself! Will they find a way to make him share?
Raa Raa and the Banana Balloons. Animation set in the Jingly Jangly Jungle. It's Banana Day in the Jingly Jangly Jungle, and all the friends are playing Banana Day games.
The Extra Mile. Detective Brewster works to help Wilson find Koko's award ribbon.
Episode 25. Comedy sketch show for younger viewers. Newsreader Arthur Sleep and sports reporter Keith Fitt both have fun spinning on their chairs.
Animal Machines. Grace shows off three amazing machines that are all like animals.
Listen to Our Song! The Game Catchers land on the Amusement Park Planet to play freezing ball. But a local alien doesn't want to play because he has had a disagreement with his friends.
Leafy Sea Dragons. Animated deep sea adventures with Captain Barnacles and his explorers. Two young leafy sea dragons are accidentally brought onboard the Octopod.
The Tale of the Wriggly Worms. Animated series. When Peter makes a rash promise to appease an angry Tommy Brock, he and his friends find themselves worming for their lives.
The Yoga Badge. Animated preschool series. The Squirrels are all hyped up with bundles of energy. Duggee needs to calm them down. Fortunately, he has his yoga badge.
Pippen Tells the Truth. Pippen pretends to have some strange symptoms so that she can relax in the recovery room.
Dangle Disaster. Evil Pea has set a trap for the Tatocar but gets herself and Corn trapped instead.
Mission Penalty. Weasy and the Chipmunk wreck the farm. The sentence? Community service!
Joist Hoist. Swoppiton Bridge is falling down - can Mojo and Bo help Nori fix it in time?
Pass the Parcel. Lucky's dad changes the rules of pass the parcel back to having one prize in the middle.
Seesaw. Dad has rudely plonked himself on one end of the seesaw. So Bluey and Bingo round up the entire playground to help flip him off, but they still need to find one more friend.
Brinicle's Shopping Spree. The Piris try to change Brinicle's wasteful ways, but their recycling plan hits a snag.
Andy and the Bowerbird. Preschool wildlife series. When Andy accidentally breaks a bowerbird nest, he heads to the jungles of Papua New Guinea so he can learn how to make a new one.
Waffle Tries to Be Good. Preschool comedy drama series. When Jess takes Evie for her first school visit, Waffle goes along too. He tries to behave, but it's hard for a Wonder Dog!
The Baby Wish. Rafi's wish turns her dads into babies. She realises being grown up means having responsibility - and that chores can be fun when mixed with dancing.
It's Time for Pottery. Jared has a special plant which needs a pot, so JoJo makes him one in a pottery class. When the pot is knocked onto the floor and breaks, Gran Gran has a plan.
The Art of Pink. Animation. The art gallery is holding a celebration of the colour pink. Sarah is keen to take part.
The Brilliant Surprise. Stop-motion animation. When Tiny Clanger receives a message from the Iron Chicken that 'it's coming', she is mystified as to what the 'it' might be.
Wind. It's a windy day, and MeMo and BaBa have fun playing with the wind in many different ways: blowing pinwheels, flying kites, and even making musical wind chimes with the Yummies.
Ninky Nonk or Pinky Ponk. In a magical forest, colourful characters have adventures. Everyone rides on the Ninky Nonk except the Tombliboos, who ride in the Pinky Ponk instead.
Katherine and Nat Sciver-Brunt - The Perfect Fit. England cricketers Katherine and Nat Sciver-Brunt read a Bedtime Story about a triangle trying to fit in.
